WHAT IS PDS?
------------

PDS is a nonlinear programming code for unconstrained problems, which only
uses function values (no derivatives needed).  It is especially intended to be
used in a parallel computing environment.

PDS was written by V. Torczon (email: va@cs.wm.edu). 
